canonical:
  title: 冊世子賀牋
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 天生歧嶷之姿春宮貳極民仰貞良之德寶冊揚庭凡屬瞻聆悉均蹈舞恭惟英姿玉裕偉量淵冲視膳問安志專承順存心養性學就緝煕履玆昌辰茂膺純嘏伏念濫持使節遙想儲闈載賡輝閏之歌切効康寧之祝
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 冊世子賀牋
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 天生歧嶷之姿。春宮貳極。民仰貞良之德。寶冊揚庭。凡屬瞻聆。悉均蹈舞。恭惟英姿玉裕。偉量淵冲。視膳問安。志專承順。存心養性。學就緝煕。履玆昌辰。茂膺純嘏。伏念濫持使節。遙想儲闈。載賡輝閏之歌。切効康寧之祝。
korean:
  title: 책 세자 하 전
  author: 이첨
  language: kor
  text: 하늘이 비범한 이물을 내시어 춘궁(春宮)이 이극(貳極)이 되시었고 백성들이 정랑(貞良)한 덕을 우러름에 보책(寶冊)이 왕정(王庭)에 들날리오니, 무릇 보고 듣는 자 모두 기뻐 춤추옵나이다. 공손히 생각하옵건대, 옥같이 온유(溫裕)하신 영자(英姿)와 연못처럼 깊으신 도량으로 친선(親膳)하시고 문안(問安)하심에 효성이 지극하옵시고 존심(存心)하고 양성(養性)하심에 학문이 일취월장하옵시니, 이 성례(盛禮)의 날을 당하시어 순수한 복을 그지없이 받으시리이다. 얻드려 생각하옵건대, 외람되게 사절(使節)을 가지고, 먼 곳에서 멀리 세자궁(世子宮)을 상상하면서, 휘윤(輝潤)의 노래를 이어 노래하여 간절히 강녕(康寧)의 축원을 대신하옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0530&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 휘윤(輝潤)의 노래 : '
    value: “돌이 옥을 품으면 산이 빛나고, 옥이 산에 있으면 나무가 번질번질한다.[石蘊玉而山輝玉在山而木潤]”란 시구가 있는데, 여기서는 세자(世子)의 인품을 옥에 비유한 것이다.
english:
  title: Petition of Congratulations on the Investiture of the Crown Prince
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Heaven has bestowed upon him a nature of remarkable distinction,
    and the Eastern Palace ascends to share the imperial throne.
    The people revere his virtuous character of integrity and goodness,
    and the precious seal is raised aloft in the royal court.
    All who witness and hear this rejoice and dance in celebration.

    With reverent contemplation, I observe:
    His noble bearing gentle as jade, his wisdom deep as a still pond.
    In attending to the royal table and inquiring after health,
    his filial piety shines with perfect devotion.
    In cultivating his mind and nurturing his nature,
    his learning grows with each passing season.
    Upon this auspicious day of great ceremony,
    may he receive boundless and pure blessings.

    Though I am unworthy to bear this embassy,
    from distant lands I turn my gaze toward the Eastern Palace,
    joining my voice to songs of radiance and lustrous virtue,
    that I might offer in earnest these wishes for his eternal health and peace.
  footnotes:
    - 'The ''song of radiance and luster'' alludes to the poetic lines: ''When stone contains jade, the mountain gleams; when jade dwells in the mountain, the trees grow lustrous.'' Here, the Crown Prince''s character is likened to precious jade itself.'
    - The Eastern Palace (春宮) is a traditional title for the residence and position of the Crown Prince in East Asian courts.
